            <odd>
              <p>(The first two-thirds of the volume devoted to activities at Camp Winnecomack near Munsonville, New Hampshire, in 1913. Five sheets relating to Mrs. Lambert's first year at Helen Newberry dormitory, 1915-1916. Six sheets devoted to the summer activities, 1916-1917. Four sheets show the Library School class of 1917 its August picnic and the library bindery with William C. Holland.)</p>
